      step3DetailIntro: "Communicate with suppliers through the chat interface. Follow the step-by-step instructions below to exchange messages, clarify order details, and coordinate collaboration effectively.",
      step3DetailStep1Title: "Step 1: Access the Chat Interface",
      step3DetailStep1Text: "First, you need to log in to your account. Once logged in, you can access the chat interface in two ways: 1) Click the envelope icon in the top menu to open the mail/messages section, or 2) Click on your avatar at the bottom of the screen - a menu will appear where you can select 'Messages' to open the chat interface. From there, you can also access conversations from the supplier profile page by clicking the 'Start Conversation' or 'Contact Supplier' button.",
      step3DetailStep2Title: "Step 2: Initiate or Continue Conversation",
      step3DetailStep2Text: "If starting a new conversation, select the supplier you want to communicate with from your list of contacts or suppliers. If continuing an existing conversation, click on the conversation thread to open the chat window.",
      step3DetailStep3Title: "Step 3: Exchange Messages",
      step3DetailStep3Text: "Type your message in the message input field at the bottom of the chat window. You can ask questions, clarify order details, discuss specifications, or coordinate project requirements. You can also send quote requests or send quotes directly from the chat interface. Click 'Send' or press Enter to send your message. Messages are delivered in real-time, allowing for immediate communication.",
      step3DetailStep4Title: "Step 4: Manage Conversations and Requests",
      step3DetailStep4Text: "Use the chat interface to send quote requests, review received quotes, and discuss terms and conditions. You can attach files, share project documents, or reference specific items from your project. All conversation history is saved for future reference.",
